From: Paul Gortmaker <paul.gortmaker@windriver.com>
drivers class: conditional mutex_init
    
This should really be converted to using non-underscore versions
of mutex_init, so that the difference between _mutex_init() and
__mutex_init() on RT vs. non-RT remains a hidden delta.

At least this way, you can go back and compile non-RT within
the same tree w/o changing the source.
    
Signed-off-by: Paul Gortmaker <paul.gortmaker@windriver.com>

---
 drivers/base/class.c |    4 ++++
 1 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/base/class.c b/drivers/base/class.c
index cc5e28c..e12d57b 100644
--- a/drivers/base/class.c
+++ b/drivers/base/class.c
@@ -148,7 +148,11 @@ int __class_register(struct class *cls, struct lock_class_key *key)
 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&cp->class_devices);
 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&cp->class_interfaces);
 	kset_init(&cp->class_dirs);
+#ifdef CONFIG_PREEMPT_RT
+	_mutex_init(&cp->class_mutex, "struct class mutex", key);
+#else
 	__mutex_init(&cp->class_mutex, "struct class mutex", key);
+#endif
 	error = kobject_set_name(&cp->class_subsys.kobj, "%s", cls->name);
 	if (error) {
 		kfree(cp);
